pull_request.body:
To test this:

Sync with Sitecore and add layouts/placeholder settings/carmax/* to your sitecore instance.


Create a dummy Navigable page in Sitecore.
Open Experience Editor.
Remove all renderings and save.
Click the Top Hashed area (should be Header) and click the "Add to here" 
You should only see the "header" rendering as a selectable rendering.
Repeat for header-navigation placeholder.
Repeat for footer and footer-navigation placeholder.

comment.body:
Feels like this code is trying to return 2 things -

1. Get SEO friendly URL
2. Also return true/false based on requestedPath == friendlyPath for whether or not permanent redirect is required.

The task 2 above should be the concern of ItemResolver and not SeoLinkProvider. Refactoring to that effect would help maintain that separation of concerns as well as keep GetFriendlyUrl() method honest and return valid URL always (and not conditionally return string.Empty).

Hope that makes sense. If you need any further clarification, please let me know!
